summary: Ship please! I'm 32, black haired and blue eyed. I love vintage culture and fashion from the 50s. I love old rock and roll like...
question: Ship please! I'm 32, black haired and blue eyed. I love vintage culture and fashion from the 50s. I love old rock and roll like Elvis Presley. Thanks love!
answer:
I ship you with my chaotic bb, Kevin Lomax from “The Devil’s Advocate”.

· You met Kevin in a small diner while you were taking a vacation in Florida

· Kevin was single at the time and ultimately took a liking to you

· The both of you have a total vintage aesthetic

· He loves to wear a nice tweed jacket and put on his glasses because he knows how much you love the way he looks

· He loves how classy you tend to look with your older styled outfits, and sometimes you two will end up role playing at home or when you’re on a date

· You both love spending nights dancing together by your record player, allowing you to break out you vast collection of some timeless oldies

· He treats you like his queen, making sure he spends enough time with you

· Despite how serious he is about his career, you come first

· He takes you out on little dates. Like to the movies, a picnic in the park, or a walk along the Florida coastline

· Kevin’s mom, Alice, really likes you, much more than any other girl he’s ever brought home

· Because you love fashion from the 50s, Alice is more than willing to let you borrow/use/have her many different things she wore during the decade

· He always goes to you for a second opinion for everything, including his cases and which clients he should represent

· It was because of you that he decided to decline John Milton’s offer and stay at home in Florida rather than move to New York

· The two of you make a cute couple, and Kevin loves to make sure that everyone knows you’re his

· One of the many things he loves about you are your eyes. He can’t help but get lost in them every time you look at him

~Playlist~

  • “Love Me Tender” by Elvis
  • “Crazy Little Thing Called Love” by Queen
  • “Fly Me To The Moon (In Other Words)” by Frank Sinatra
  • “Ring of Fire” by Johnny Cash
  • “Fever” by Peggy Lee
  • “When I Fall In Love” by Nat King Cole
